The{War Memorial}was unveiled in 1919. It was built to commemorate those who died in the{First World War.
It contains the names of all the men, from or connected with Sanday, who were killed in that Great War. There are{50}names of first world war victims but there were only{2}names from the{Second World War}added on a separate plaque after 1945.
The memorial is situated at the cross roads near the Community Centre; and every year, on Remembrance Sunday, {there is a Remembrance Service}held under the auspices of the local branch of{The Royal British Legion. {
